        advanced: 'Apply steampunk aesthetic blending Victorian elegance with industrial machinery. Metal colors: brass (#b5a642), copper (#b87333), bronze (#cd7f32), iron gray (#48494b) - use gradients for metallic sheen. Mechanical elements: gears and cogs (SVG) as decorative elements, exposed mechanisms, pistons, valves. Textures: aged leather (brown with subtle grain), vintage paper (cream with foxing spots), riveted metal panels. Typography: Victorian display fonts (Playfair Display, Cinzel, Old Standard TT), decorative flourishes, old-style numerals. Borders: ornate Victorian frames, mechanical brackets, riveted edges (circular pattern along border). Color palette: sepia (amber-800, orange-900), browns, cream, with brass/copper accents. Gauges and dials: circular analog instruments, pressure meters, clock faces. Buttons: large, industrial with beveled metal appearance, visible screws. Wood and leather: panels with wood grain, leather straps with buckles and stitching. Steam effects: subtle animated wisps, valve releases. Light: warm, gas-lamp glow (amber shadows, vignette), Edison bulb aesthetic. Interactive: mechanical movements on hover (gears rotate, needles move), satisfying clunk animations. Layered depth: foreground machinery over background texture. SVG heavily for mechanical parts. Implementation: complex layered design, optimize for performance. Accessibility: maintain readability despite busy aesthetic, clear interactive indicators.'
