        advanced: 'Apply blueprint/technical drawing aesthetic with engineering precision. Background: blueprint blue (#0c2340, #1a365d) or dark gray for modern take, overlaid with precise grid pattern (CSS repeating gradient or SVG). Line work: thin, precise lines in white or light blue (#a0c4ff), consistent stroke width (1-2px). Drawing style: technical illustration approach - orthographic views, cross-sections, exploded diagrams. Dimension lines: annotation lines with arrows, measurement labels, leader lines pointing to details. Typography: engineering/technical fonts (Roboto Mono, IBM Plex Mono, DIN), all caps for labels, precise spacing. Annotations: callout labels with lines connecting to elements, numbered references, spec tables. Geometric precision: perfect circles (compass-drawn appearance), precise angles, mathematical curves. Cross-sections: elements showing internal structure, hatching patterns for materials. Title block: formal drawing title area with project info, date, revision. Border: thick outer border with tick marks, drawing number. Interactive: zoom to detail on hover, reveal hidden dimensions. Modern elements: combine with digital data overlays, animated construction. Color coding: different systems in different line colors (mechanical, electrical, etc). Implementation: SVG for technical drawings, CSS Grid for precise layout. Accessibility: ensure line weights visible, provide alternative text for technical diagrams.'
