        advanced: 'Apply geometric abstract aesthetic with bold, artistic composition. Shape vocabulary: circles, triangles, rectangles, polygons - perfect geometry, no organic curves. Overlapping: shapes layer with mix-blend-mode effects (multiply, overlay, screen) creating new colors at intersections. Color strategy: bold, confident palette - limit to 3-5 colors maximum, can be complementary, analogous, or triadic. Each shape solid color or subtle gradient. Transparency: semi-transparent shapes (opacity-50 to opacity-80) creating depth where overlapping. Composition: asymmetric balance, tension between shapes, intentional negative space. Scale contrast: mix of large dominant shapes with smaller accent shapes. Positioning: shapes can extend beyond container (overflow-hidden on parent), suggesting continuation. Depth: larger background shapes, smaller foreground shapes, shadow optional for separation. Animation: subtle shape movement, rotation, scale pulsing for dynamic feel. Grid option: underlying grid visible through transparent shapes. Mondrian option: strict horizontal/vertical only, primary colors plus black grid. Kandinsky option: more playful, circles and triangles dominant, warm colors. 3D option: shapes with perspective transforms suggesting depth. Implementation: CSS shapes or SVG, absolute positioning for layering. Accessibility: abstract art can be inaccessible - ensure any functional elements remain clear, provide alternative context where needed.'
