        advanced: 'Apply glitch art aesthetic with intentional digital corruption and databending. RGB split: offset color channels using multiple text-shadows or pseudo-elements with different colors (red left, cyan right offset by 2-5px). Scan line distortion: horizontal slices displaced using clip-path animations, pseudo-random translateX values. Pixel sorting: vertical streaks effect using repeating-linear-gradient with sharp color bands. Block displacement: random rectangular sections offset using CSS clip-path with animation. Static noise: SVG filter with feTurbulence, or canvas-generated noise overlay, animated opacity. VHS effects: tracking lines (horizontal white bars moving vertically), color bleeding, tape warping at edges. Text corruption: use CSS to randomly hide/show characters, replace with symbols (█▓▒░), letterSpacing glitches. Fragment effect: content broken into offset pieces using clip-path. Data visualization: binary/hex strings as decorative elements, corrupted file aesthetics. Animation: erratic, non-smooth movements using steps() timing or random keyframe values. Sound visualization: audio waveform distortion graphics. Color: high contrast, neon on black, or desaturated with color pops. Implementation: heavy CSS animations, SVG filters, optional canvas for real-time effects. CRITICAL: respect prefers-reduced-motion - glitch effects can trigger seizures, provide static fallback. Ensure core content remains readable despite effects.'
