        advanced: 'Apply Figma aesthetic with design tool patterns. Chrome: bg-[#2c2c2c] for panels, bg-[#1e1e1e] for toolbar. Canvas: bg-[#e5e5e5] checkered or solid, centered artboard. Panels: w-64 fixed, scrollable content, collapsible sections. Toolbar: horizontal, icon buttons with tooltips, grouped with dividers. Layer tree: indented list, visibility/lock icons, selection highlight. Properties: labeled inputs in grid, section headers collapsible. Input fields: compact, dark bg-[#3c3c3c], light text, number scrubbing. Color picker: swatch button opening popover, hex/rgba inputs. Dropdowns: dark themed, checkmark for selected. Selection: blue handles on corners/edges, rotation handle top. Context menu: dark, sections with dividers, keyboard shortcuts right-aligned. Zoom: bottom-left percentage, zoom to fit buttons. Rulers: optional, tick marks with numbers. Grid: toggle overlay with grid lines. Tabs: panel section switcher, bottom border indicator. Resize handles: panel edges draggable. Keyboard shortcuts: extensive, shown in tooltips. Prototype: separate mode with flow connections. Comments: pin markers on canvas, sidebar thread.'
