        advanced: 'Apply GitHub aesthetic with code platform patterns. Colors: white bg (light), bg-[#0d1117] (dark), green for additions, red for deletions, blue links. Header: black bar, logo, search with slash hint, nav items. Repository header: name with org, visibility badge, stars/forks counts, watch dropdown. Tab bar: Code, Issues, PRs, Actions, etc with counts. File tree: folder icons, file icons by extension, file/folder names. Code view: line numbers, syntax highlighting, blame view, history. Blob: raw/blame/history buttons, file size, copy button. Diff: split or unified view, +/- line markers, expand context buttons. Issues: title, labels (colored pills), assignees (avatars), milestones. PR: status checks (green check, yellow dot, red x), review states, merge button. Comments: markdown rendered, reactions, edit/delete for own. Activity graph: green squares calendar heatmap. Profile: avatar, bio, pinned repos, contribution graph. Labels: colored bg with contrast text, editable. Actions: workflow runs list, status icons, duration. Markdown: proper rendering with checkboxes, tables, code blocks. Branch dropdown: current branch, search, switch. Clone: HTTPS/SSH tabs, copy button.'
